{"asctime": "2026-04-14T17:48:56Z", "levelname": "INFO", "name": "infrastructure.ai.claude_session_tutor", "message": "Calling Claude session tutor", "session_id": "sess_447c4b87668e", "gagne_event": 4, "ped_state": "confusion", "message_count": 3}
{"asctime": "2026-04-14T17:49:03Z", "levelname": "INFO", "name": "httpx", "message": "HTTP Request: POST https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages \"HTTP/1.1 200 OK\""}
{"asctime": "2026-04-14T17:49:03Z", "levelname": "INFO", "name": "infrastructure.ai.claude_session_tutor", "message": "Claude session tutor response received", "session_id": "sess_447c4b87668e", "elapsed_s": 7.03, "response_snippet": "\u00a1No te preocupes, lo vamos a ver juntos paso a paso! \ud83d\ude0a\n\n---\n\nImagina que **f(x) es una m\u00e1quina**:\n\n- **Le metes un n\u00famero** (por ejemplo, el 4) \u2192 la m\u00e1quina lo procesa \u2192 **te devuelve otro n\u00famero**.\n- La \"receta\" de la m\u00e1quina es la f\u00f3rmula, por ejemplo: **f(x) = 3x + 2**\n\nEntonces, **evaluar f(4)**", "usage": {"input_tokens": 892, "output_tokens": 309}}
{"asctime": "2026-04-14T17:49:03Z", "levelname": "INFO", "name": "persistence", "message": "Session saved", "session_id": "sess_447c4b87668e", "status": "active"}
